headline: Zoetis Avian Influenza Vaccine Secures Conditional Approval In US For Use In Chickens
summary: On Friday, the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) Center for Veterinary Biologics (CVB) issued Zoetis Inc (NYSE:ZTS) a conditional license for its Avian Influenza Vaccine, H5N2 Subtype, Killed Virus. The vaccine is labeled for use in chickens. The conditional license was granted on the demonstration of safety, purity, and reasonable expectation of efficacy based on serology data.
